    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I see. You mentioned earlier that critics worry about the economic burden on lower-income people. If the consensus is that this is a \"vital\" and \"necessary\" tool, how do planners reconcile that with the fact that it essentially functions as a regressive tax? Does the environmental necessity eventually outweigh the economic hardship for those commuters, or is that just a trade-off they have to accept?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
